You can do a game

00:33:05.500 --> 00:33:09.050
that's all-- requires
nothing but 100% effort.

00:33:09.050 --> 00:33:11.887
And in a sense, the play is
who decides to play that game.

00:33:11.887 --> 00:33:13.720
The people who are
willing to put themselves

00:33:13.720 --> 00:33:17.830
through 100% effort all the
time, they voluntarily do that.

00:33:17.830 --> 00:33:19.551
And so you've found
your audience.

00:33:19.551 --> 00:33:21.550
I'm not saying you couldn't
do a game like that.

00:33:21.550 --> 00:33:24.175
I'm saying that it's likely that
in the course of most people's

00:33:24.175 --> 00:33:28.840
gameplay, they're going to
have this need to-- a game

00:33:28.840 --> 00:33:31.200
where you get on the rails
and the clock is going,

00:33:31.200 --> 00:33:33.700
and you guys [INAUDIBLE].

00:33:33.700 --> 00:33:35.370
That's why there's
usually plateaus

00:33:35.370 --> 00:33:36.370
of some kind or another.

00:33:36.370 --> 00:33:38.550
There's an acknowledgement
that people

00:33:38.550 --> 00:33:40.220
need to stop and take a breath.

00:33:40.220 --> 00:33:44.080
Even if it's just a
plateau, a savepoint,

00:33:44.080 --> 00:33:45.650
there's some
acknowledgement of that.

00:33:45.650 --> 00:33:47.150
I think games where
there's actually

00:33:47.150 --> 00:33:50.660
some combination of really
intense play and more

00:33:50.660 --> 00:33:54.240
relaxed play can sometimes
be more satisfying.

00:33:54.240 --> 00:33:57.310
So I'm not saying that a
game can't be all hard--

00:33:57.310 --> 00:33:59.061
or the other side of
it, Farmville clearly

00:33:59.061 --> 00:34:01.310
was very popular with lots
of people who really wanted

00:34:01.310 --> 00:34:02.610
to do kind of mindless stuff.

00:34:02.610 --> 00:34:04.490
I guess we all have
the need sometimes

00:34:04.490 --> 00:34:07.700
for non-taxing-- so there's
nothing wrong with a game which

00:34:07.700 --> 00:34:11.480
requires almost all
in or very little in.

00:34:11.480 --> 00:34:14.650
It's just that the
reality is, the player is

00:34:14.650 --> 00:34:17.073
going to move fluidly from
one state to the other.

00:34:17.073 --> 00:34:19.489
And if your game can accommodate
that, so much the better.

