AUDIENCE: Yeah.

00:47:26.700 --> 00:47:28.950
So the current
state of our game,

00:47:28.950 --> 00:47:30.869
we spent a lot of time
thinking about design

00:47:30.869 --> 00:47:34.140
and how exactly we
want to do things.

00:47:34.140 --> 00:47:36.760
So we're currently
making sort of a game

00:47:36.760 --> 00:47:39.010
where you control--
or don't control.

00:47:39.010 --> 00:47:41.090
You take care of a
bunch of villages.

00:47:41.090 --> 00:47:43.320
So you see different villages,
how infected they are,

00:47:43.320 --> 00:47:45.153
and how many people are
dying sort of thing,

00:47:45.153 --> 00:47:47.820
and then implement measures
to prevent cholera spreading.

00:47:47.820 --> 00:47:50.460
So you give people soap
to wash their hands

00:47:50.460 --> 00:47:54.365
or set restroom facilities,
or use vaccination,

00:47:54.365 --> 00:47:56.050
and that sort of thing.

00:47:56.050 --> 00:47:58.800
And so a lot of the
feedback that we

00:47:58.800 --> 00:48:01.590
got on a lot of questions
that we're facing basically

00:48:01.590 --> 00:48:04.935
revolves around the issue of
making this game realistic

00:48:04.935 --> 00:48:08.660
versus making this game
more fun sort of thing.

00:48:08.660 --> 00:48:11.970
So you can make a really
unrealistic game that

00:48:11.970 --> 00:48:13.990
can be tons of fun,
but we also want

00:48:13.990 --> 00:48:16.073
to stick to reality because
at the end of the day,

00:48:16.073 --> 00:48:18.860
we do want to teach the people
that are playing how to prevent

00:48:18.860 --> 00:48:20.320
cholera from spreading.

00:48:20.320 --> 00:48:22.740
So there's sort of this
trade-off that we have to make.

00:48:22.740 --> 00:48:25.320
And the second trade
off is sort of like you

00:48:25.320 --> 00:48:29.370
can make a blantanty educational
game that just throws back

00:48:29.370 --> 00:48:31.578
at you that can sort of be
fun for the first time you

00:48:31.578 --> 00:48:33.578
play it, but doesn't have
a lot of replay value.

00:48:33.578 --> 00:48:36.639
And it's sort of hard to make
a great educational game that

00:48:36.639 --> 00:48:37.930
also has a lot of replay value.

00:48:37.930 --> 00:48:40.424
So we're thinking, maybe
consider maybe we don't

00:48:40.424 --> 00:48:41.590
want that much replay value.

00:48:41.590 --> 00:48:45.120
Maybe this is a game that these
people will play once or twice,

00:48:45.120 --> 00:48:47.620
learn what they need to learn,
and then never play it again.

00:48:47.620 --> 00:48:50.559
So it's sort of trade-offs
that we need to think about.

