00:51:40.430 --> 00:51:40.930
Heat Wave.

00:51:48.585 --> 00:51:49.126
AUDIENCE: Hi.

00:51:49.126 --> 00:51:51.430
So as you guys have
all heard, Heat Wave

00:51:51.430 --> 00:51:53.800
is going to be a game
that will hopefully

00:51:53.800 --> 00:51:58.210
be used to help Red Cross
volunteers help people in areas

00:51:58.210 --> 00:52:00.068
that are either
suffering from or about

00:52:00.068 --> 00:52:02.320
to suffer from a heat wave.

00:52:02.320 --> 00:52:05.710
So what we did was
we decided we wanted

00:52:05.710 --> 00:52:09.700
to test out a very simple
digital prototype, not

00:52:09.700 --> 00:52:12.890
with the same type action
as our final prototype,

00:52:12.890 --> 00:52:16.260
but not in Unity
because having a working

00:52:16.260 --> 00:52:18.051
game in Unity at this
point we didn't think

00:52:18.051 --> 00:52:19.380
is a viable option.

00:52:19.380 --> 00:52:21.450
So we made a Python
test base game.

00:52:21.450 --> 00:52:23.860
And people were
able to choose what

00:52:23.860 --> 00:52:26.430
they were going to do based
on the scenario and the people

00:52:26.430 --> 00:52:28.360
they were interacting with.

00:52:28.360 --> 00:52:33.450
And what we really want to
test it was how does this work.

00:52:33.450 --> 00:52:36.300
Is playing a good way to learn?

00:52:36.300 --> 00:52:39.490
And if so, how can we make more
learning come out of the fact

00:52:39.490 --> 00:52:42.620
that they're playing a game
and then making these choices.

00:52:42.620 --> 00:52:46.740
So what we did was we showed
people, and a lot of times,

00:52:46.740 --> 00:52:48.156
people noticed
right away, well, I

00:52:48.156 --> 00:52:50.590
don't want to sit there
and do nothing, which is

00:52:50.590 --> 00:52:52.180
what we wanted them to notice.

00:52:52.180 --> 00:52:56.110
And oh, this person passed
out even though they were

00:52:56.110 --> 00:52:57.613
only outside for three hours.

00:52:57.613 --> 00:52:58.365
Why was that?

00:52:58.365 --> 00:53:00.140
So we did see a lot of that.

00:53:00.140 --> 00:53:02.850
But something we didn't
see was people sometimes

00:53:02.850 --> 00:53:04.185
got stuck in a pattern.

00:53:04.185 --> 00:53:06.700
It's just like, well, I'm always
going to do the same thing.

00:53:06.700 --> 00:53:07.845
And then they don't
get different results

00:53:07.845 --> 00:53:09.680
and they don't really
learn anything.

00:53:09.680 --> 00:53:12.950
So we want to give people more
interesting options and more

00:53:12.950 --> 00:53:15.470
options in our actual game
so that they try more things

00:53:15.470 --> 00:53:16.340
and they learn more.

00:53:16.340 --> 00:53:18.967
So that's what
we're going to do.

